definitions.definition: One who is not part of a community or organization .
examples: While the initiated easily understand the symbols, they are wholly inaccessible to outsiders .

definitions.definition: A newcomer with little or no experience in an organization or community.
examples: Seeing the mess professional politicians have made of things is it any wonder the electorate is beginning to prefer outsiders ?

definitions.definition: A competitor or contestant who has little chance of winning ; a long shot .
examples: Johnny was an outsider at this year's karate tournament, but he still managed to win second place out of sheer determination.

definitions.definition: The heel or end piece of a loaf of bread .
